
<Lesson stage="3" page="10" type="Reading Check">
<APageParagraph activityIntroClip="uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3"  pencil="p3" skipIntro="true">
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
         <text>We have had many pioneers in our country and some have had a big impact on us all, like Henry Ford.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
       <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence> 
      <sentence>
         <text>When he was young, Ford was curious and tinkered with things.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>As an adult, Ford became an engineer in Detroit.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He was able to combine his time and money to work with car engines.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
       <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>   
      <sentence>
         <text>In 1903, Henry Ford started the Ford Motor Company.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He reached his dream of making a car that was affordable and reliable when he made the Model T in 1908.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>This car was very popular.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
  </paragraph>
  <paragraph>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
         <text>Ford changed car-making completely in 1913.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
       <sentence>
         <text>He made a moving assembly line.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>This took the car parts by moving belt to the workers.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The speed was constant to keep the line running smoothly.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>His clever idea in car-making reduced substantially the time it took to make a car, and made it cheap to make.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
  </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Ford's company became the largest car-maker in the world because there was no competition that could beat the Model T.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Ford's company helped to change America because cities changed and suburbs grew; the highway system expanded.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>We connected to a love of the open road.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>Ford saw many of these changes before his death in 1947.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
